 A Day In The Life The Sr. Principal Business Analyst supports various phases of product development from initial conception through to deployment and continuous improvement. They will work closely with the Product Owner and the project team, facilitating and executing a seamless integration of business processes with advanced data-driven insights. Key to this role is the ability to understand and document both current and future business needs, collaborating with internal stakeholders and external service providers to identify and implement the most effective IT solutions. The analyst must possess a strong analytical capability to manage and interpret data from diverse sources, ensuring data integrity and usefulness for making strategic decisions. The Sr. Principal Business Analyst helps ensure that data and analytics solutions meet user requirements and are in line with the strategic goals of the organization. Their work not only involves rigorous analysis and documentation but also ongoing collaboration and communication across various levels of the organization to champion the adoption of data-centric business solutions.
 


 As a Sr. Principal Business Analyst you will:
 

Supports the Product Owner and project team through various product phases like Process Analysis, Requirements, User Acceptance Testing, Training, Deployment, and Continuous Improvement.
Documents current and emerging business needs and works with internal and external service providers to define and deliver data and analytics solutions.
Participates in sessions to gather business context from Product Owners, analyze, document findings.
Documents business requirements, use stories, and technical requirements.
Collaborates with internal customers to ensure user requirements are complete and concise, confirming that changes and enhancements meet technical specifications and user requirements.
Performs data analysis on different data sources, consolidating multiple data sets and analyzing the data accurately and efficiently.
Performs business process analysis to define how data and analytic solutions should be configured to meet those needs.
Performs data analysis to review and analyze business performance prior to and post the deployment of data and analytic solutions. Using SQL, BI Reports and ad-hoc analysis within PowerBI, Tableau, Excel, and other applications.
Maps current processes to the desired state and identifies gaps such as program functions, output requirements, input requirements and sources, data conversion strategies, and system techniques and controls.
Assists with the development of test designs and develops test cases.
Assists with the development and maintenance of product and project documentation including internal project status and conceptual business communications materials.
This position may have direct reports depending on the project and organizational structure.



 What We Need From You


Bachelor's Degree Computer Science, Data Science, Mathematics, Engineering, or a related field. Req
8+ years of experience as a highly technical Business Analyst, Product Manager, Solutions Architect, Business Systems Analyst supporting data and analytic software development projects. Required
Experience working with Agile development methodology. Strong understanding of Agile methodologies and experience working in an Agile and hybrid development environment.
Strong prior participation in the design, development, and implementation of enterprise data and analytic solutions. A working understanding of applying data and analytics to improve business processes.
Ability to elicit, articulate and document process modeling, business requirements, description of business context using scenarios and user stories.
Strong foundational knowledge of Agile Methodology in application, as well as Product Development and the Software Development Life Cycle.
Proven experience with business and technical requirements analysis, elicitation, modeling, verification, and methodology development
Experience using JIRA and Confluence to support workflow.
Experience in various data and reporting tools such as SQL, PowerBI, Tableau, and Excel
Strong demonstrated experience with Microsoft applications such as PowerPoint and can pull together clear, concise, and convincing presentations using mockups, data, and written context.


 Physical and Environmental Requirements

   The physical requirements described here are representative of those that must be met by an associate to successfully perform the essential functions of the job. While performing the duties of the job, the associate is required on a daily basis to analyze and interpret data, communicate, and remain in a stationary position for a significant amount of the work day and frequently access, input, and retrieve information from the computer and other office productivity devices. The associate is regularly required to move about the office and around the corporate campus. The associate must frequently move up to 10 pounds and occasionally move up to 25 pounds.

ABOUT ADACTION
Founded in 2013, AdAction is a leader in performance-based mobile app marketing, delivering premium users at scale for top brands and app developers worldwide. We foster a fast-paced, collaborative, and growth-oriented environment, where team members thrive on autonomy and making meaningful contributions. While we are a remote-first company we are currently only hiring in Colorado, Illinois, Texas, and North Carolina.
 POSITION SUMMARY
AdAction is seeking a highly motivated and proactive individual to join our team as a Senior Data Analyst. This role plays a crucial part in our company's growth and modernization efforts, with ample opportunities for professional development and advancement. The ideal candidate will possess strong technical skills, a passion for problem-solving, and the ability to thrive in a dynamic and ambiguous environment.
 This is a contract-to-hire position with an initial contract period of six months. At the conclusion of the contract, there is potential for full-time employment based on performance and business needs.
 RESPONSIBILITIES

Contribute to the modernization efforts of our data processes, including the transition to frameworks such as Airbyte, Airflow, and DBT.


    Collaborate with cross-functional teams to automate and streamline BI processes, eliminating reliance on adhoc reports.
   


    Proactively identify opportunities to enhance data analytics processes and systems, recommending and implementing solutions to optimize efficiency and effectiveness.
   


    Utilize technical expertise in DBT, Airflow, Python, Git, AWS, and various data visualization tools (e.g., Tableau, Looker, QuickSight) to enhance data analytics capabilities.
   


    Work closely with engineers to ensure seamless integration of BI processes within our data pipeline framework.
   


    Design and implement A/B testing experiments to derive actionable insights, with a strong understanding of analytical events and how to leverage them effectively. Prior experience in working with event-driven data streams is a plus.
   


    Act as a strategic advisor to cross-functional teams, leveraging data analysis to provide actionable recommendations and insights that drive informed decision-making and support long-term business objectives.
   


    Partner with the business to provide consultancy and translate the business needs to design and develop tools, techniques, metrics, and dashboards for insights and data visualization.
   


    Collaborate closely with product teams in a data mesh environment, going beyond traditional reporting to engage in problem-solving activities that require cross-functional interaction and the development of innovative data solutions.
   
Stay abreast of industry trends and emerging technologies in data analytics, continuously exploring new methodologies and tools to drive innovation and maintain a competitive edge.

 EXPERIENCE & QUALIFICATIONS

Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics, or a related field.


    3+ years of experience in business intelligence, data analysis, or a similar role.
   


    Proficiency in DBT (or familiarity with stored procedures and data warehouse operations), Airflow, Python, Git, and AWS.
   


    Experience with data visualization tools such as Tableau, Looker, or QuickSight.
   


    Familiarity with databases including Redshift, Snowflake, and Postgres.
   


    Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to thrive in a fast-paced, ambiguous environment.
   
Excellent communication and collaboration skills, with the ability to work effectively in cross-functional teams.

 ADDITIONAL INFORMATION
This contract role offers significant opportunities for growth and advancement within the company, including the potential for full-time employment in roles focused on data science, machine learning, and other areas of data analytics.
We are looking for individuals who are proactive, driven, and able to navigate ambiguity with ease.

Position Description




    Under general supervision, the Senior Data Analyst will perform various administrative, analytical, and reporting functions in support of departmental programs, projects, and services. Individuals in this role will gather, consolidate, process, track, and analyze data and information using automated systems, utilizing data findings to provide recommendations regarding departmental policies, procedures, and services. The Senior Data Analyst is expected to collaborate with stakeholders to ensure data accuracy, support strategic decision-making, and contribute to the continuous improvement of departmental processes and systems.

 Data Collection & Analysis: Collects, queries, and analyzes data using standard statistical tools, applications, methods, and techniques.  Stakeholder Communication & Collaboration: Communicates with various individuals and entities, including collaborating with development teams to design business intelligence solutions for gathering, storing, and retrieving data and information related to criminal justice programs, projects, and services.
 System Requirements & Reporting: Performs additional tasks such as preparing system requirements to address business information needs, and developing dashboards, reports, and presentations to effectively communicate data insights and support decision-making.
 Data Support & Troubleshooting: Serves as a knowledgeable point of contact for handling data-related inquiries, including troubleshooting issues and advising users on data conflicts and proper usage.

  Job Description Summary
  The Wildlife Futures Program (WFP), a wildlife health partnership between the University of Pennsylvania’s School of Veterinary Medicine (Penn Vet) and the Pennsylvania Game Commission (PGC) is seeking a Data Analyst to join our team. The Data Analyst will be responsible for ongoing development of the Shared Wildlife Health Information System (SWHIS), a cloud-based application for us by state fish and wildlife agencies in managing, visualizing, and interpreting their wildlife health data. Specifically, they will contribute to the back-end cloud-based infrastructure management and developing and testing of new features in partnership with the Geospatial Solutions team at the Timmons Group. The Data Analyst will support current SWHIS stakeholders (Users) by identifying “bugs,” and cleaning data for upload to the system, and the position will proactively engage and onboard new stakeholders through presentations and one-on-one meetings. In addition, the Data Analyst will support the database needs and requests for individual and program-level data collecting and management within the Wildlife Futures Program including, data from disease surveillance, diagnostics, research, and biobanking. Participation in the preparation of scientific papers and grant proposals is also required.  The position is based remotely. Position is contingent upon grant funding.
 

  Job Description
 

  Job Responsibilities
 

Work with Timmons Group to contribute to back-end cloud-based infrastructure management to support existing SWHIS stakeholders and to develop and test new features.
Work with Wildlife Futures personnel to integrate existing database systems used for managing the program’s wildlife health data from field collection to biobanking
Promote SWHIS to new stakeholder groups through presentations and one-on-one meetings.
Work with Wildlife Futures personnel to support database and data visualization needs for individual and project-level data collecting, management, and reporting.
Provide materials and writing support for grant submissions to support further development of the Shared Wildlife Health Information System.
Other duties and responsibilities as assigned



  Qualifications
 

Bachelor’s degree is required, preferably in a quantitative or health science discipline and 2-4 years of professional experience. Demonstrated experience manipulating complex data, including data mining, cleaning, organizing, querying, and analyzing. Fluency in Python and R Shiny required. Experience with animal health, diagnostic data preferred. Excellent communication skills and ability to convey findings to a broad audience (e.g. state agency staff, academic researchers), including quarterly report for users and key stakeholders and routine progress reporting to funders. Proactive, flexible, and innovative; can adapt to changing priorities and needs with an ability to work under short deadlines. Ability to work collaboratively with a diverse team is required.

 The Opportunity

The Data Analyst II, within the Mass General Brigham Enterprise Analytics (EA) Department, is responsible for identifying, querying, analyzing, and visualizing data through reports and presentations, a variety of data to support operations, quality and performance measurement initiatives throughout Mass General Brigham, including its acute and specialty hospitals around greater Boston. The Data Analyst II will be responsible for providing analytics insights to leadership at various levels within the organization. The position requires close collaboration and dialogue with clinical personnel, various analytic groups, and hospital and system leadership.

The Enterprise Analytics Department supports data and reporting across most domains of the hospital operations and could include areas such as patient satisfaction, patient safety, clinical outcomes, asset utilization, and more. The successful Data Analyst II will create lasting relationships with hospital leadership by becoming highly proficient in the data within his or her designated areas of expertise. Regular responsibilities include gathering requirements, performing qualitative and quantitative analyses, finding and querying complex data, and sharing data and results in a digestible, visually appealing, way.

In addition, the Data Analyst II will share best practice methodologies with other analysts and train end-users on various tools as needed, growing the team’s wealth of knowledge and documentation. The team mainly relies on Microsoft SQL Server, Tableau, the Microsoft Office suite, and is partnering with the MGB Digital data platform teams on a journey to build a new data platform with Microsoft Azure Cloud and Snowflake, and leverages other tools and technologies on an as needed basis.

 Principal Duties and Responsibilities

1. Elicits data and reporting requirements from hospital leadership, clinicians, and other staff, using interviews, document analysis, requirements workshops, site visits, use cases, scenarios, data analysis, task, and workflow analysis.
2. Queries and analyzes data from hospital systems such as our electronic medical record system (Epic), enterprise data warehouse (EDW), external websites, and more, to glean meaningful insights and produce actionable reports for internal customers.
3. Presents data and analyses to key stakeholder groups and hospital leadership, including creating materials for and giving presentations as needed.
4. Works with EA and Digital staff in design, maintenance, and distribution of reports while also overseeing ad hoc data analyses and new report development as needed.
5. Works with EA and Digital staff to continually improve our analytical capabilities with SQL, Tableau, and other analytic platforms, which includes but not limited to dashboard and report development, QA of existing reports, and documentation of system functionality.
6. Performs comprehensive quality assurance, ensuring that data and reports meet end user specifications and are accurate and reliable.
7. Works with new and existing EA analysts to share knowledge in methods of data analysis, summarization, and presentation. Trains end-users on key analytic and reporting systems and databases.
8. Partner with MGB Digital teams to leverage existing tools, methods, and processes in order to deliver timely information to operations stakeholders across MGB, including leveraging Microsoft Azure, Snowflake, and Informatica cloud tools.
9. Effectively recognizes when additional help or guidance is needed and seeks it out proactively.
10. Represents EA on internal and external committees or task forces as needed.
11. Performs all other related duties as required.



 Qualifications

1. Bachelor’s degree in management, information systems, statistics, or equivalent experience.
2. At least 3-5 years of experience, preferably in a related analytics position.
3. Healthcare knowledge, particularly as it pertains to electronic medical record data, is preferred but not required.
4. Working knowledge of relational databases, SQL, data visualization, and Business Intelligence tools such as Tableau and proficiency in at least one of these areas.
5. Knowledge and application of statistical analyses including variance analysis and statistical significance preferred.
6. Developing knowledge and application of workflows and data structures of underlying MGB systems, especially Epic, preferred.
7. Experience with Epic Clarity, Caboodle, and/or Cogito a plus
8. Project management skills and/or experience a plus.
9. Proficiency with Microsoft Office Suite, including Word, Excel and PowerPoint.

 Skills and Abilities

1. Strong ability to work and communicate effectively with staff at various levels within the organization.
2. Experience with querying, manipulating, cleansing, and statistically analyzing large data sets using tools such as SQL Server Management Studio.
3. Proficiency with Excel, manipulating large data sets and synthesizing into digestible information, including polished visualizations.
4. Experience presenting data through the building of dashboards and reports using business intelligence tools such as Tableau (preferred). With direction from more senior teammates, create data visualizations that are suitable for presentation to senior leaders.
5. Ability to clearly communicate complex and sensitive data to hospital leaders as well as peers.
6. Strong written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to tailor message to individuals and audiences throughout the institution.
7. Strong organizational skills, with the ability to focus detailed concentrated effort on multiple projects and take direction regarding appropriate prioritization.
8. Possesses initiative and ability to work independently while thriving in a setting requiring collaboration and teamwork for maximal efficiency and effectiveness.
9. Attention to detail that ensures follow through on all initiatives implemented, and all projects undertaken.
10. Ability to effectively respond to time sensitive issues and meet deadlines.

As a Data Analyst/IT Consultant, you will serve as a technology expert and a pivotal figure in advancing data services. - Excellent written and verbal communication skills with the ability to address diverse audiences.
- Proven track record of working independently and as a technical lead.

  Job Description
 


  SS&C Intralinks is looking for a Temporary Data Analyst to advance our data preparation and labeling efforts in support of AI product initiatives. This role will engage with both engineering and product management teams as we build AI product functionality for products within SS&C Intralinks’ Alternative Investments business. The SS&C Intralinks Alternative Investments business supports private capital and hedge fund firms. Our objective is to provide solutions that help clients improve their investor communication/reporting, investor onboarding and fund marketing efforts as well as support their private capital M&A activities.
 

  The Intralinks Alternative Investments business is a strategic growth lever for the company with industry leading and innovative products. In this role, you will be part of our efforts to leverage the latest in AI innovation to enable greater productivity for our customers.
 

  You will be using your knowledge of financial statements to help with data preparation, classification and labeling efforts for AI model research and training. This role lies at a unique intersection of business analysis, product management and data science as it applies to the financial services industry and may provide a pathway to career advancement along one of those directions. Additionally, you will have the opportunity to contribute to fast paced AI driven innovation as part of a highly collaborative team of stakeholders.
 


  Day to Day:
 

Partner with product management to understand, scope and deliver on data preparation needs.
Identify, classify and label data and content within financial documents for AI model training.
Use tools created by AI engineering team as well as Intralinks products to prepare and validate alternative investments data.
Document and communicate progress of activity across different projects with internal stakeholders.

Minimum of 2 years completion towards a Bachelor's degree in finance, computer science or business, or in MBA program (a plus)
Detail oriented with analytical and problem solving skills.
Basic familiarity with financial statements.
Basic familiarity with AI and data analysis.

Our Third-Party COE Reporting & Analytics team not only understands how process, technology and systems work, but how the information is used to generate valuable and actionable insights for our program stakeholders. Drive Data strategy initiatives

Excellent Visual Design skills with sensitivity to user-system interaction – experience in developing reporting solutions towards complex multi-paneled, interactive dashboards.

Ability to communicate complex ideas in a simple manner to a global audience.

  Position Title:
  Data Analyst I - SLCPD
 
  Job Description:
  SLCPD is looking for a new crime analyst to join our team! In this role, you'd be responsible for providing strategic, tactical, and operational support and analytics to patrol, investigations, special operations, and command staff. Responsibilities include identifying emergent crime patterns and series, analyzing criminal activity and contributing to intervention efforts, communicating critical intelligence to officers, completing complex analyses joining datasets from disparate sources, and producing reports/dashboards/maps that meet the needs of internal and external stakeholders.  Incumbents at this level possess the skill to assist the organization with data-driven decision-making.
 

  About the Position:
 


   Candidates with a bachelor's degree in data/computer science, statistics/mathematics, social sciences, criminology/criminal justice, or closely related field are encouraged to apply! Read more about the minimum requirements below. Successful candidates will be familiar with visualization software such as ArcGIS, Tableau or Power BI, and/or coding languages such as SQL, Python, or R.
  


   This position is 40 hours per week, generally Monday through Friday, 8am to 5pm. There is an option to work four days a week, ten hours per day or five days a week, eight hours per day. This position currently allows for a hybrid work schedule, although it is subject to change per department need. Although rare, the role may require holiday and weekend work.
  


   About the Team:
  

   SLCPD's Crime Intel & Analysis Unit (CIAU) has seven team players led by the department's data science and research director. Together, the team handles intelligence gathering and data requests. Every week they are challenged to develop creative solutions and think outside of the box. Sometimes this means reviewing camera footage, database searching, and using other investigative tools to identify suspects. Other times they leverage technology so leaders have real-time information and the statistics needed to drive decisions.
  


 This position will remain open until 10/3/2024.
  


   Position Salary Range:
  

   $62,506 - $88,244
  


   This position is eligible for full city benefits, including:
  



     Health, dental, vision, and life insurance
    


     13 paid holidays per year
    


     Paid vacation and personal leave
    


     Six weeks of paid parental leave
    


     Retirement contributions toward a pension plan or 401(k)
    


     A robust EAP that provides emotional support, work-life solutions, legal guidance, and financial resources, including up to 15 counseling sessions for you and your household family members at no cost
    


     Tuition reimbursement
    


     Discounted supplemental benefits like pet insurance, legal services, and shopping.
    



   Key Responsibilities:
  



     Works with data in multiple systems, develops appropriate datasets, applies analytical best practices, ensures accuracy, and creates reports, dashboards, and maps that meet the needs of the end users.
    


     Serves as primary contact and subject matter expert for patrol divisions and investigations. Provides on-demand support based on quickly evolving crime patterns and the emerging needs of city leaders.
    


     Participates in the investigative process through analytical examination of data, intelligence, and evidence, to identify offenders and link cases in support of successful case resolution.
    


     Performs comprehensive research of persons, places, and vehicles in criminal cases
    


     Conducts open-source research and data analysis of social media for potential criminal activity and/or threats to the community.
    


     Presents clear and concise findings to stakeholders.
    


     Consistently delivers work products on time.
    


     Troubleshoots data challenges and reconciles discrepancies with creative problem solving.
    


     Develops trust and partnerships within the department to deliver value-added reporting and intelligence that reflects the strategic objectives of the organization.
    


     Handles highly sensitive information with integrity and professionalism.
    


     Performs additional duties as assigned.
    



   Minimum Qualifications:
  



     Graduation from an accredited four-year college or university with a bachelor’s degree in the Social Sciences, Data/Computer Science, Statistics/Mathematics, Criminology/Criminal Justice, or closely related field.
    


     Directly related work experience may be substituted for education on a year-for-year basis.
    


     Familiarity with visualization software such as ArcGIS, Tableau, and Power BI, and/or coding languages such as SQL, Python, or R.
    


     Ability to collect and analyze data/trends and make appropriate recommendations to further a department’s goals. Possess strong data analysis skills and project management skills.
    


     Excellent problem-solving skills and ability to think creatively with numbers. When encountering roadblocks, communicates the issue and considers alternate solutions.
    


     Strong verbal and written communication skills. Effectively communicates with people of diverse backgrounds within and outside an organization.
    


     Knowledge of the theory, principles, practices, and methods of crime analysis and criminal behavior.
    


     Manage conflicting priorities with different timelines, multitask, and effectively adapt to change.
    


     Demonstrates critical thinking skills by asking questions and identifying opportunities for improvement. Always looking to learn and enhance personal and team performance.
    


     Proficient in Microsoft Office.
    


     Able to learn new software and analytic techniques and apply it to future projects.
    



   Desired Qualifications:
  



     In depth knowledge of statistics, quantitative analysis, and telling stories with data.
    


     Professional experience using analytical software, databases, and systems used to gather analytics and intelligence such as ArcGIS, Tableau, Power BI, SQL, Python, or R.
    


     Professional certifications including International Association of Crime Analysts (IACA).
    


     Technical certifications in programming such as SQL, Python, etc.
    



   Working Conditions:
  



     Generally comfortable working conditions requiring light physical effort. Intermittent sitting, standing, and walking, and frequent use of a computer, telephone, and other standard office equipment.
    


     May work four days a week, ten hours per day or five days a week, eight hours per day.
    


     May require shift work, including holidays and weekends.

Description
The Global Product Management (GPM) organization is responsible for business performance of all research products. The Research Business Analytics (RBA) team is part of GPM and performs analysis related to all aspects of Gartner’s Research. This includes client value drivers: Research content, research interaction, and the research role in conferences and events. RBA also supports the Research & Advisory (R&A) organization by enabling and performing analysis running from client retention analytics, associate performance analytics, budget, and financial analysis (in partnership with the finance organization), and client demand sensing. We power fact-based decision making by providing data, insights, and analytic tools to continuously improve our business – operationally and strategically.   We are looking for an Analyst who is a strong analytical problem solver, has technical understanding of data/data systems and an exceptional team player to be part of our growing team.
This role will primarily focus on ownership of end-to-end deliverables on content and/or interaction and related assets e.g. documents, tools, advisory conversations, proposal reviews etc, including business and operational insights. Initiatives/projects involve data definition, data pull, technical understanding of Gartner data, analyze for insights, build recommendations, visualize data, scale through automate visualizations and reporting. Example objectives are

Build end-to-end dashboards that communicate the performance of our content/interactions including root causes and insights of upcoming trends, areas of bright spots and opportunity
Standardize and automate the top reads for a document or ways we measure reach of a document or impact of interaction etc, across the entitled licensed user base considering target role / industry / geo, the priorities navigator, and other factors.
Build mechanisms to measure current performance and improvement opportunities, of our research assets
Improve content and interaction reporting (e.g., scorecard, operation reviews, adhoc requests from product and R&A), dashboards, and automation

This is an exciting opportunity to be hands-on in our efforts to fuel Gartner’s revenue growth and retention through Gartner’s world-class, must-have content and extraordinary and timely client interactions.
What you’ll do:

Build expertise to be the center of excellence on Gartner research assets data, with deep knowledge of the data across source systems, the data warehouse, and dashboards / reports so analysis is unassailable, and other Gartner teams rely on the data we provide and guidance on how to use it.

Summary: 
The Field Business Intelligence Team plays a meaningful role in measuring the health and success of our company’s distribution system through reporting, data analytics and insights to tell a story with data using sophisticated techniques and visualization. Provides quantitative and qualitative data analysis and reporting of patterns, insights, and trends to decision-makers in order to drive business decisions and address business questions

Implement best practices, methodologies, standards and processes and share across teams. Occasionally contribute to the development there of.

Contributes to the growth & development of the organization through actively sharing result & insights across the teams and with Business Clients

Regularly applies new perspectives, creative problem solving, and inter-departmental connections to improve analytical capabilities
Embraces continuous learning, curiosity, and ambiguity


Qualifications: 

Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, MIS, Mathematics, Statistics, Business or related field
At least 5 years of progressively responsible experience in research and data analysis, application of statistical research techniques, report or application development that support business decisions/outcomes
Expertise in development and application of analytical tools such as SAS, SQL, MS Excel, R, Python or other tool
Visualization tooling like PowerBI or Tableau
Ability to access, gather, and analyze data from multiple internal and external sources to drive insights into business problems, decisions, and performance

  Position Title:
  Data Analyst I - SLCPD
 
  Job Description:
  SLCPD is looking for a new crime analyst to join our team! In this role, you'd be responsible for providing strategic, tactical, and operational support and analytics to patrol, investigations, special operations, and command staff. Responsibilities include identifying emergent crime patterns and series, analyzing criminal activity and contributing to intervention efforts, communicating critical intelligence to officers, completing complex analyses joining datasets from disparate sources, and producing reports/dashboards/maps that meet the needs of internal and external stakeholders.  Incumbents at this level possess the skill to assist the organization with data-driven decision-making.
 

  About the Position:
 


   Candidates with a bachelor's degree in data/computer science, statistics/mathematics, social sciences, criminology/criminal justice, or closely related field are encouraged to apply! Read more about the minimum requirements below. Successful candidates will be familiar with visualization software such as ArcGIS, Tableau or Power BI, and/or coding languages such as SQL, Python, or R.
  


   This position is 40 hours per week, generally Monday through Friday, 8am to 5pm. There is an option to work four days a week, ten hours per day or five days a week, eight hours per day. This position currently allows for a hybrid work schedule, although it is subject to change per department need. Although rare, the role may require holiday and weekend work.
  


   About the Team:
  

   SLCPD's Crime Intel & Analysis Unit (CIAU) has seven team players led by the department's data science and research director. Together, the team handles intelligence gathering and data requests. Every week they are challenged to develop creative solutions and think outside of the box. Sometimes this means reviewing camera footage, database searching, and using other investigative tools to identify suspects. Other times they leverage technology so leaders have real-time information and the statistics needed to drive decisions.
  


 This position will remain open until 10/3/2024.
  


   Position Salary Range:
  

   $62,506 - $88,244
  


   This position is eligible for full city benefits, including:
  



     Health, dental, vision, and life insurance
    


     13 paid holidays per year
    


     Paid vacation and personal leave
    


     Six weeks of paid parental leave
    


     Retirement contributions toward a pension plan or 401(k)
    


     A robust EAP that provides emotional support, work-life solutions, legal guidance, and financial resources, including up to 15 counseling sessions for you and your household family members at no cost
    


     Tuition reimbursement
    


     Discounted supplemental benefits like pet insurance, legal services, and shopping.
    



   Key Responsibilities:
  



     Works with data in multiple systems, develops appropriate datasets, applies analytical best practices, ensures accuracy, and creates reports, dashboards, and maps that meet the needs of the end users.
    


     Serves as primary contact and subject matter expert for patrol divisions and investigations. Provides on-demand support based on quickly evolving crime patterns and the emerging needs of city leaders.
    


     Participates in the investigative process through analytical examination of data, intelligence, and evidence, to identify offenders and link cases in support of successful case resolution.
    


     Performs comprehensive research of persons, places, and vehicles in criminal cases
    


     Conducts open-source research and data analysis of social media for potential criminal activity and/or threats to the community.
    


     Presents clear and concise findings to stakeholders.
    


     Consistently delivers work products on time.
    


     Troubleshoots data challenges and reconciles discrepancies with creative problem solving.
    


     Develops trust and partnerships within the department to deliver value-added reporting and intelligence that reflects the strategic objectives of the organization.
    


     Handles highly sensitive information with integrity and professionalism.
    


     Performs additional duties as assigned.
    



   Minimum Qualifications:
  



     Graduation from an accredited four-year college or university with a bachelor’s degree in the Social Sciences, Data/Computer Science, Statistics/Mathematics, Criminology/Criminal Justice, or closely related field.
    


     Directly related work experience may be substituted for education on a year-for-year basis.
    


     Familiarity with visualization software such as ArcGIS, Tableau, and Power BI, and/or coding languages such as SQL, Python, or R.
    


     Ability to collect and analyze data/trends and make appropriate recommendations to further a department’s goals. Possess strong data analysis skills and project management skills.
    


     Excellent problem-solving skills and ability to think creatively with numbers. When encountering roadblocks, communicates the issue and considers alternate solutions.
    


     Strong verbal and written communication skills. Effectively communicates with people of diverse backgrounds within and outside an organization.
    


     Knowledge of the theory, principles, practices, and methods of crime analysis and criminal behavior.
    


     Manage conflicting priorities with different timelines, multitask, and effectively adapt to change.
    


     Demonstrates critical thinking skills by asking questions and identifying opportunities for improvement. Always looking to learn and enhance personal and team performance.
    


     Proficient in Microsoft Office.
    


     Able to learn new software and analytic techniques and apply it to future projects.
    



   Desired Qualifications:
  



     In depth knowledge of statistics, quantitative analysis, and telling stories with data.
    


     Professional experience using analytical software, databases, and systems used to gather analytics and intelligence such as ArcGIS, Tableau, Power BI, SQL, Python, or R.
    


     Professional certifications including International Association of Crime Analysts (IACA).
    


     Technical certifications in programming such as SQL, Python, etc.
    



   Working Conditions:
  



     Generally comfortable working conditions requiring light physical effort. Intermittent sitting, standing, and walking, and frequent use of a computer, telephone, and other standard office equipment.
    


     May work four days a week, ten hours per day or five days a week, eight hours per day.
    


     May require shift work, including holidays and weekends.
    


     On occasion may be required to respond outside normal working hours to meet the needs of the department.
    



   Career Ladder:
  

   After successful performance as a Data Analyst I, and fully satisfying the minimum qualifications of the Data Analyst II, incumbents may be advanced to the Data Analyst II based on supervisor/manager recommendation, availability of funds, and approval of the Department Administration and the concurrence of the Department of Human Resources
  


   Offers of employment are contingent on successful completion of a criminal background check in accordance with City and department policy and applicable law. Criminal offenses will be reviewed on a case-by-case basis and do not automatically disqualify a candidate from City employment.

NinjaHoldings was founded in 2017 by a team seeking to revolutionize the way everyday Americans interact with financial services. Through our CreditNinja and NinjaCard brands, we empower people overlooked by traditional financial institutions to take control of their finances via a full suite of digital banking and lending products, providing incentives and rewards along the way as we guide them on a path to financial improvement. Through our Edge brand, we help companies better understand their customers by offering a package of bespoke underwriting, fraud detection, and analytics services. With offices in Chicago, Miami, and around the world through the power of remote work, we are a lean and innovative team always seeking like-minded talent to join us in our fight to disrupt consumer finance.
Job Summary
NinjaHoldings is seeking an experienced business analyst to join our Risk & Analytics team. This is a critical position that will be responsible for designing, creating, and managing decisions in our rules engine platform. The candidate will manage the implementation of business rules throughout our application funnel to ensure we are always making optimal decisions.
Key Responsibilities:

Design, implement, and thoroughly test new decisions in the customer acquisition and underwriting rules engine, collaborating with Analytics and Engineering to ensure a seamless integration
Maintain the rules engine; developing and testing changes to the rules when necessary to optimize originations and loan performance; and ensuring the decisions are working as intended
Monitor key funnel metrics, reports, and dashboards to evaluate the performance of our products and understand the root causes of changes
Establish funnel performance metrics and develop automated reporting and alerting using SQL and Python
Conduct analysis using advanced data analytics to evaluate trends in funnel performance and fraud metrics and provide strategy recommendations to optimize performance based on company objectives
Support underwriting by having an understanding of the rules for different customer segments and products
Communicate concise and actionable business strategies to senior management

Requirements:

Bachelor's degree in a quantitative or business discipline (e.g., math, statistics, finance, economics, engineering, or other quantitative fields)
3+ years of experience working with business stakeholders and technical teams to design and implement solutions
2+ years of experience working with python and SQL for reporting and data analysis in a professional setting
SQL proficiency and experience working with relational databases, query authoring, as well as familiarity with a variety of databases
Strong quantitative and problem-solving skills with key attention to detail
Experience supporting and working with cross-functional teams in a dynamic environment
Ability to work effectively while managing multiple projects with tight deadlines, understand the project requirements with minimal guidance, and follow through to completion

Additional Pluses, but Not Requirements:

Experience working with specialty finance or FinTech
Experience with low code rules engine platforms

Benefits:

Competitive salary and benefits package
Flexible, remote work
Fun, fast-paced work environment
Dynamic start-up culture
Ability to make an immediate impact in a growth stage company
Convenient downtown Chicago office located in the heart of the city
Equal opportunity employer

 Responsibilities
 Position Summary:
With minimal direction and considerable latitude for independent judgment, performs routine and non-routine duties requiring advanced technical and analytical skills and proficiency to support the education activities for the Graduate Programs (currently including MPH, MS-CI, MS-EPI, MS-HSR, EPI PHD, HSR PHD, Preventive Medicine Residency and multiple certificates) in the Department of Public Health Sciences (PHS) within the School of Medicine and Dentistry.  Responsibilities:
 Student Records

Develop, manage, track and monitor all official, confidential academic records of current SMD graduate students, and Residents in the Department of Public Health Sciences ensuring the accuracy, integrity and security of all records. Work with Office of Graduate Education and Postdoctoral Affairs, and Graduate Medical Education Office on the preparation and analysis of enrollment data.

 Educational Program Data Support

Responsible for maintaining PHS database of applicants and current students/residents and alumni of PHS Graduate Programs (MPH, MS-CI, MS-EPI, MS-HSR, EPI PHD, HSR PHD, Preventive Medicine Residency and multiple certificates).

 Recruitment, Admissions, and Alumni Relations

Transfer SOPHAS applications to Slate.
Track the processing of all application and admission materials through various admissions systems for the different educational programs. Utilize systems to manage applicant data, and provide reports and required information to relevant PHS committees and the Graduate Admissions Office.
Coordinate with the Offices of Graduate Education and Postdoctoral Affairs and Graduate Medical Education on admissions and application processes.
Assist the Academic Administrator with managing the PhD interview weekend process and assist with Residency Match.
Maintain alumni database, update records, assist with alumni survey activities, and support efforts to build and maintain PHS education programs alumni network(s)

Obtain and maintain 'expert level' knowledge of Box and Microsoft Office 365 cloud platforms and associated MS 365 applications.

Proficiency in database management and reporting software required

 Overview: 
  Toxicology Data Analyst Responsibilities: 
 The Toxicology Data Analyst will extract and analyze data/information from internal and public access databases and documents for toxicological assessment. They are expected to have a working knowledge of biology, biochemistry, and/or toxicology.
They will create, maintain, and analyze databases of in vivo and in vitro test method results for development and/or validation of new approach methods for toxicity testing. They will develop and coordinate project timelines associated with the validation and implementation of these methods. They are expected to assist in all aspects of data analysis, including data curation, data management, statistical evaluation, and preparation for/conducting analyses using predefined computational workflows.
Dissemination of information needed by U.S. governmental committees and regulatory agencies, stakeholder working groups, peer review panels, and test method developers is an essential part of this position. As is taking meeting minutes and preparing meeting summaries for distribution internally, and externally (scientific community and the public). Likewise, preparation of scientific and technical documents (e.g., presentations, reports, workshop summaries, manuscripts, operating procedures) are core components of this position. The Toxicology Data Analyst will work in a team environment where cooperation and a professional attitude are essential. Other duties will be assigned as needed. Qualifications: 
  Required

M.S./B.S. in related scientific field with at least 0/2 years post-degree experience in biology/biochemistry/toxicology and/or data analysis
Demonstrated proficiency in the use of scientific databases such as EPA’s CompTox Chemicals Dashboard and OECD eChemPortal
Strong experience and proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite
Excellent verbal and written communication skills


 Preferred


Strong technical writing and editing skills
Functions well independently and in a team environment
Proficiency in R and/or Python
Familiarity with contract research and regulatory testing requirements

Please include a description of relevant experience in the areas of required proficiency described above.
A successful team member will be a service-oriented team player who is able to work on a variety of projects within the area of pharmacology and toxicology. They will work cooperatively with diverse teams and communicate their science effectively to non-technical clients. This position is based in RTP, NC and is eligible for remote work in the U.S.


 This position could be offered at different levels for candidates who qualify with a combination of advanced levels of education and/or years of experience. The salary range will adjust along with the level of the role to match the person’s relevant experience and/or education level.

   Our Data & Systems Analyst will conduct data analysis and enhance our systems.
  


Description



     Hi, I’m Khadijah, Senior Manager of Growth & Analytics
    


 I will be leading the hiring process for this role, which is a critical addition to our team as we continue to fuel our growth engine. Thank you for your interest and for taking the time to learn more about us.
    


 —



Who We Are:


     Switchyards is the world’s first neighborhood work club. We're creating places to do our best thinking and most productive work. Near home. Around friends and neighbors. Always open — 24/7.
    


 Based in Atlanta and venture-funded, we’ve created a new consumer category for the future of work. With big plans to open work clubs across the country, we are becoming one of the iconic brands of our generation.
    


 In our next phase, growth = oxygen, we’re on the hunt for a tenacious Data & Systems Analyst, who is passionate about using insights and data science to drive customer-centric growth.
    


 The role:


     As a key fixture of the Growth & Analytics team, you’ll conduct complex analyses and recommend actionable insights that will catalyze membership growth and turn loyal members into raving Switchyard fanatics. You will also optimize and scale our systems, enabling us to operate more efficiently as we open 200 clubs over the next 5 years.
    


 What you’ll do:


     In your day to day, you will analyze trends, identify opportunities, develop reports and implement technology solutions that will streamline our operations and support our growth strategy.



     This role is at an exciting intersection of business, technology and data. If you are all about getting work done creatively and collaboratively — you live and breathe data —and are excited about growing the next world-class brand, come join our Growth & Analytics team.
    


 What you bring:


Relentless curiosity. You don't shy away from the unknown. You constantly ask ‘why?’ and dig a layer deeper in pursuit of a more meaningful and nuanced answer/insight.
Facts and numbers. You are a data-driven and logical decision maker. You can make confident decisions based on hard facts and numbers.
Mathematician. You live and breathe numbers. And you outperform others when it comes to this arena.
Adaptability. You are flexible and eager to grow. You understand that it’s necessary to adjust perspective and priorities when doing something in a unique way. You excel in “the gray.”
Bias for action. You have an ownership mindset and an outstanding ability to identify and resolve problems.
Both brains. A balance of a creative and analytical mindset. You can pull out a nugget of insightful data and ideate creative tactics to action it.



 Responsibilities:

Data Analysis & Reporting (70%)




Data Management: Oversee the integration and maintenance of data across various platforms to ensure data integrity, accuracy, and accessibility.
Analysis: Analyze operational, member, and financial data to uncover trends and performance metrics. Create reports and dashboards to monitor key KPIs, including member growth, occupancy, retention, and revenue, LTV etc.
Data-Driven Decision Making: Distill complex data into actionable insights to inform strategic decisions, such as optimizing space utilization, enhancing member experience, and identifying growth opportunities.
Regular Reporting: Develop and automate regular reports on key metrics (e.g., membership numbers, occupancy rates, revenue)
Forecasting & Planning: Use data models to project future trends, guiding decisions on expansion, pricing strategies, and resource allocation.
Data Champion: Serve as the in-house subject matter expert on data and analytics, shepherding a data-driven mindset across the organization.



Systems Management & Optimization (30%)




Systems Management: Own the management, maintenance, and optimization of internal systems, including testing, troubleshooting, and implementing improvements.
Process Automation: Develop and implement automated workflows between systems (e.g., membership databases, payment systems, booking software) to reduce manual tasks and errors. Utilize scripting, APIs, and third-party tools as needed.
Technology Advancement: Proactively identify and recommend new tools to enhance our tech stack and data infrastructure.





 Qualifications:


Bachelor’s degree in a quantitative, business, STEM, or research discipline. OR a degree in another field with a strong aptitude for analytical / quantitative thinking.
3+ years of professional experience, preferably in analytics, data science, business intelligence, or data insights roles
Proficient in navigating large datasets, acquiring, cleansing data from multiple sources. Comfortable working with both structured and unstructured data.
Hands-on experience with relational databases (e.g., MySQL, PostgreSQL) and NoSQL databases.
Strong working knowledge of a programming language (e.g., SQL, SAS, R, Python, Javascript) with the ability to write clean, maintainable, and efficient code.
Basic understanding of data architecture and engineering techniques, including data modeling, schema design, and query optimization.



 Nice to Haves:


Data visualization skills and familiarity with BI tools (Tableau, Looker Studio)
Familiarity with cloud data infrastructure (AWS, Google BigQuery)
Ability to deploy, monitor, troubleshoot applications in a production environment.



 Note: Switchyards is an Equal Employment Opportunity and Affirmative Action Employer. Qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender perception or identity, national origin, age, marital status, protected veteran status, or disability status.

Strong written, verbal, and interpersonal communication skills, enabling effective interaction with stakeholders and other business users, with a demonstrated ability to communicate complex data concepts clearly and understandably.

We are currently seeking an BI Analyst, Supply Chain Digital Operations. This position requires a deep understanding of business intelligence and supply chain analytics within a manufacturing environment. The Analyst will lead KPI generation of supply chain and procurement activities to drive visibility, innovation, efficiency, and agility across the supply chain function.
Key Responsibilities

Partnering with supply chain stakeholder disciplines (ex. Procurement, planning, logistics, program management, etc) and cross-functional organizations to identify KPIs and analysis that can drive visibility and efficiency to deliver value to the company.


Work with stakeholders to identify analytical gaps in supply chain management


Foster cross-functional support for initiative activities


Propose appropriate working structures, timelines, and project plans necessary to track and manage progress


Strategic Leadership:


Develop and execute a data-driven strategy to enhance supply chain operations, improve forecasting accuracy, reduce costs, and mitigate risks.


Collaborate with leadership to align BI and digital initiatives with business objectives and overall company strategy.


Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including IT, operations, and procurement, to integrate BI solutions seamlessly into existing environment.


Stakeholder Engagement:


Collaborate with internal stakeholders, including supply chain leaders, operations managers, and business executives, to understand their requirements and priorities and translate them into data-driven solutions.


Analytics:


Oversee the collection, processing, and analysis of large datasets from multiple sources to extract actionable insights and drive data-driven decision-making.


Stay abreast of emerging trends and best practices in data visualization and apply to solve supply chain challenges.

You Bring

Bachelor’s degree computer science, supply chain management, engineering, finance, in business administration, or related field

· Technical expertise in data extraction, exploration, modeling, and visualization using SQL, Python / R, PowerBI, Tableau, etc
· Strong analytical skills and familiarity with financial decision models and technical/business case creation (Cash-to-Cash conversion, ROI, TCO, etc.)
· System thinker that can clearly articulate technical requirements between brand and technical teams
· Experience in SAP or other MRP/ERP programs
· Possesses a thorough understanding of supply and demand material requirements planning, procurement, sourcing, logistics, materials management & warehousing.

Proven track record of BI analysis, with at least 5 years of experience in supply chain BI development.


Strong business acumen and strategic thinking skills, with the ability to translate business requirements into data-driven solutions that deliver tangible value and ROI.


Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to influence and collaborate effectively with stakeholders at all levels of the organization.


Proven ability to drive change and lead cross-functional initiatives in a dynamic and fast-paced environment.


Knowledge of supply chain management principles, processes, and technologies, with a passion for driving innovation and continuous improvement.

· Familiarity with best practices around successful software implementation

Title: Marketing Database Analyst
 Job Summary:
We are looking for an experienced Marketing Database Analyst to join our team at Miccosukee Casino & Resort. As a valued team member, we are committed to delivering a memorable, impressive, caring, committed and original experience for our guests, our team members, and community. We uphold this commitment by providing a safe and enjoyable workplace where YOU are our number one priority. It is the MICCO way.
Miccosukee Casino & Resort is actively expanding, introducing a range of new features including a Poker room, a revamped player rewards program, the TEMPT lounge, La Brisa Restaurant, and two exclusive slot zones. These additions aim to elevate the overall customer experience, blending technology with service for enhanced delivery, and creating unique, aspirational opportunities for both our guests and team members. To realize our bold expansion plans, we need individuals who share our dedication to service and commitment to providing an unforgettable experience. If you're passionate about service and looking for a role that offers fair compensation, excellent benefits, internal growth prospects, and a fun work environment, we're eager to get to know you.

 Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in Marketing, Statistics, Computer Science, or a related field.
Experience in database management and data analysis.
Proficiency in data analysis tools (e.g., SQL, Excel, SAS) and knowledge of CRM systems.
Strong analytical skills and ability to translate complex data into actionable insights.
Excellent communication and presentation skills.
Knowledge of marketing principles and digital marketing trends.
Experience with data visualization tools is a plus.
Detail-oriented with a strong analytical mindset.
Proactive and able to work independently as well as part of a team.
Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to think strategically.
Maintain physical stamina and proper mental attitude while dealing effectively with guests, management, team members, and outside contacts while working under pressure and meeting deadlines.
Must be able to frequently move freely about the property, maintain manual dexterity to operate job related equipment, such as telephones, copiers, etc., withstand various activities such as frequent walking, sitting for long periods and withstand prolonged standing, stretching, bending and kneeling without restriction.
Be able to work indoors and be exposed to various environmental contaminants including smoke.
Ability to lift or carry a minimum of 20 pounds unassisted in the performance of specific tasks assigned.
Must be able to work with others, communicate well, receive direction, and provide feedback when needed to achieve department goals and objectives.
Must maintain a positive attitude toward work and interface with guests in a congenial and polite manner.
Must be able to address stressful situations with clients with dignity and the utmost tact and politeness.
Must be able to touch and handle supplies in a safe and non-hazardous manner, maintaining proper hygiene, cleanliness, and disposal methods.
English required, bilingual preferred.


 Responsibilities
The Marketing Database Analyst is responsible for managing, analyzing, and leveraging the company's database to help drive effective strategies and campaigns. This role involves extensive data analysis, reporting, segmentation, and insights generation to support objectives. All duties are to be performed in accordance with departmental and Tribal Gaming Agency policies, practices, and procedures.

Data Management: Maintain and manage the database to ensure accuracy, completeness, and accessibility of data. This includes data cleansing, deduplication, and regular updates.
Data Analysis: Conduct thorough analysis of marketing data to identify trends, patterns, and insights. Utilize statistical methods to analyze data and generate useful reports.
Segmentation and Targeting: Develop and implement segmentation strategies for campaigns. Identify target audiences based on data analysis and help tailor marketing efforts to these segments.
Campaign Analysis: Measure and analyze the effectiveness of campaigns. Provide insights on performance metrics such as customer engagement, conversion rates, and ROI.
Reporting and Visualization: Create reports and dashboards for marketing and other stakeholders. Present complex data in an understandable and visually appealing manner.
Collaboration: Work closely with teams to understand their data needs and support them with relevant data and insights. Collaborate with IT and other departments to enhance data collection and analysis capabilities.
Market Research: Assist in market research and competitive analysis to understand market trends and dynamics.
Data Governance: Ensure compliance with data privacy and protection standards. Contribute to the development of policies and best practices for data governance.
Team Members are expected to conduct and carry themselves in a professional manner at all times and to observe the Company’s standards, work requirements and rules of conduct.
Consistent and regular attendance is an essential function of this job.
Performs other related duties as assigned.


 The Casino & Resort will function seven days a week, 24 hours a day. We may find it necessary to re-schedule shifts according to our business volume. You must be willing and available to fulfill these demands
While performing the duties of this job, the team member will be regularly required to walk, stand and sit. The associate will occasionally be required to climb and use balance. Additionally, the team member will frequently be asked to use hands and arms carry and lift items. Specific vision abilities required to perform this job include close vision and distance vision.  While performing the duties of this job, the team member may experience temperature fluctuations and moderate to high levels of noise. This is a smoking environment.

  Principal Data Analyst
 
At Capital One, data is at the center of everything we do. When we launched as a startup we disrupted the credit card industry by individually personalizing every credit card offer using statistical modeling and the relational database, cutting edge technology in 1988! Fast-forward a few years, and this little innovation and our passion for data has skyrocketed us to a Fortune 200 company and a leader in the world of data-driven decision-making.

 As a Data Analyst at Capital One you will leverage analytic and technical skills to innovate, build, and maintain well-managed data solutions and capabilities to tackle business problems.

 On any given day you will be challenged on three types of work – Innovation, Business Intelligence and Data Management:

 Innovation

Use Open Source/Digital technologies to mine complex, voluminous, and different varieties of data sources and platforms
Build well-managed data solutions, tools, and capabilities to enable self-service frameworks for data consumers
Demonstrate ability to explore and quickly grasp new technologies to progress varied initiatives


 Business Intelligence

Partner with the business to provide consultancy and translate the business needs to design and develop tools, techniques, metrics, and dashboards for insights and data visualization
Drive analysis that provides meaningful insights on business strategies


 Data Management

Drive an understanding and adherence to the principles of data quality management including metadata, lineage, and business definitions
Work collaboratively with appropriate Tech teams to manage security mechanisms and data access governance
Build and execute tools to monitor and report on data quality


 Our ideal candidate will have:

Degree specialized in a Science, Technology, Engineering, Mathematics discipline
Scripting experience in (Python, R, Spark, and SQL)
Strong desire and experience with data in various forms (data warehouses/SQL, unstructured data)
Experience utilizing and developing within AWS services


 Basic Qualifications:

Currently has, or is in the process of obtaining a Bachelor’s Degree plus at least 5 years of experience in data analytics, or currently has, or is in the process of obtaining a Master’s Degree plus at least 3 years in data analytics, or currently has, or is in the process of obtaining a PhD with an expectation that required degree will be obtained on or before the scheduled start date.
At least 3 years of experience in at least one scripting language
At least 1 year of experience utilizing a business intelligence visualization tool
At least 3 years of experience in querying and analyzing and working with data languages and platforms


 Preferred Qualifications:

Master’s Degree in a Science, Technology, Engineering, Mathematics discipline
At least 4 years of experience coding in Python, R, Spark, or SQL
At least 4 years of experience working within process management and improvement methodologies – Agile, Lean, Six Sigma, etc.
At least 2 years of experience utilizing and developing within AWS services
At least 2 years of experience delivering Data Governance and Data Quality Management concepts and practices within the financial services industry

 Job Description:
The Texas Health and Human Services Commission is seeking a highly skilled Database Developer/Administrator to support the TIERS DataMart database. This position requires a professional with a minimum of 8 years of experience in database development, reporting, and performance tuning, specifically utilizing Informatica and Cognos.
Key Responsibilities:

Perform advanced metrics and reporting development in Informatica 10.5 and Cognos Analytics 11.1.
Conduct performance monitoring and tuning for the TIERS DataMart to ensure efficient storage, retrieval, and archiving of diverse data sets.
Support the planning, design, administration, and maintenance of the TIERS DataMart database, ensuring scalability and stability.
Provide database design and development support to application development teams for enhancements and new program requests.
Write and debug complex reports in Informatica and Cognos, ensuring data integrity and compliance with best practices.
Configure and monitor alerts, developing and implementing monitoring tools to address future data needs.
Develop policies and procedures for consistent implementation of database and programming best practices.
Collaborate with other teams to accomplish project goals and create necessary technical and design documentation.
Conduct system analysis, troubleshooting, and problem resolution for database-related issues.
Provide technical support for testing and implementation efforts, ensuring applications function properly and without errors.
Participate in program design, coding, and test walk-through meetings, contributing insights on technical standards and customer requirements.
Support production operations by addressing defects, conducting maintenance, and ensuring overall application reliability.

Mandatory Qualifications:

Minimum of 2 years of experience with Informatica 10.5.
Minimum of 5 years of experience developing reports in Cognos Analytics 11.1.
Minimum of 8 years of experience using Unix cron and writing Unix shell scripts.
Minimum of 8 years of experience writing moderate to advanced SQL queries.
Extensive knowledge of Oracle 19 and basic understanding of star schemas/dimensional data structures.
Exceptional technical writing skills for documentation and reporting.

Desirable Qualifications:

3 years of experience with TIERS or HHSC programs and types of assistance.

Additional Information:

Candidates may be required to work outside of normal business hours, including weekends, evenings, and holidays as needed.
Prior experience within the same department and recent project involvement is mandatory.
Candidates must provide copies of relevant certifications.

This is a critical role for ensuring the integrity and performance of the TIERS DataMart database, contributing to the overall success of housing program initiatives within the organization.

     Posting Details
    





Title


        Senior Systems & Data Analyst
       



Posting Number


        S01319JP
       



Department


        Development Operations
       



Job Summary



         The Development and Alumni Relations (DAR) Senior Systems and Data Analyst (SSDA) partners with DAR and College departments who utilize data from DAR’s Constituent Relationship Management (CRM) system and other DAR function-specific software applications in meeting fundraising and outreach/engagement objectives by providing system and data analytical, technical, and educational support for the storage, access, analysis, extraction and reporting of meaningful advancement information. The SSDA develops and maintains a data warehouse and utilizes various application data extraction tools and reporting platforms to provide highly-specific philanthropic financial, prospect, event, volunteer, relationship, biographical, membership, communication, and engagement reporting for a wide range of audiences and purposes.  Essential Functions:


Receives and manages a high-volume of deadline-critical data requests from DAR and College department staff.
Performs data extraction, manipulation, and validation/reconciliation, and builds reports using CRM application tools (query/export), data warehouse systems and MS databases (SQL, Excel, Access), and reporting platforms (Powerbi, Crystal Reports).
Partners with assigned ‘Primary Program Areas’ on cyclical and new initiatives to define the most effective and efficient use of system data and processes to track progress and drive strategic action.
Provides ongoing customer support and education of data and processes for DAR staff as well as sharing in the system, data and process ‘training’ required to onboard newer IS Analysts and assist/collaborate with projects.
Owns, designs, develops, and maintains the DARIS data warehouse for the purpose of efficient and flexible access to significant and consistent DAR data.
Produces operational reports and data extraction for both internal departments and external organizations that are required on a weekly, monthly, quarterly and annual basis.
Fully participates in the implementation of function-specific DAR (or College-wide) application systems, especially from the perspective of integration with the DAR CRM. Builds exports and imports for system customizations and integrations and validates data accuracy on a regular basis.





Education/Skills Requirements

 Description

 Are you an experienced Data Analyst, ready for a unique opportunity to grow with an environmental state agency?
Join TCEQ’s strategic and efficient Air Quality Division! We bring passion and drive to carry out our mission of protecting our state’s public health and natural resources.

 TELEWORK
This position offers an opportunity for a hybrid work schedule with a minimum 2-day work in office.

 YOUR FUTURE TEAM 
As part of TCEQ’s Office of Air, you would contribute to protecting and restoring Texas’ air quality. See details about what we do.
This position is a member of our Air Quality Division.

 KEY QUALIFICATIONS

Experience retrieving (querying), reviewing, and analyzing complex data sets
Experience developing emissions data used for air quality plans and programs
Experience managing technical or scientific environmental research projects/contracts


HERE’S WHAT YOU’LL BE DOING...

Conduct moderately complex detailed analyses of anthropogenic emissions inventory data. Develop ad hoc queries from multiple databases (State of Texas Air Reporting System and Texas Air Emissions Repository).
Develop and evaluate plan and criteria for calculating, compiling, interpreting, and conducting quality assurance on anthropogenic emissions data. Work with Emissions Assessment Section staff to revise or update data and related development methods as necessary, verifying corrections were made in database.
Prepare complex report, including State Implementation Plan (SIP) revisions, and presentations for the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA), management, legislative interests, and other stakeholders regarding air quality data and anthropogenic emissions. Presents findings to the public, other regulatory agencies, and management. Conducts peer review of technical reports, presentations, and documents.
Organize, oversee, and coordinate project activities related to the development, quality assurance, and/or evaluation of emissions data, including grant and contract development and management.
Actively works with Emissions Assessment Section staff and participates in national, state, or internal work groups to develop and improve air emissions estimates. May consult on database development projects as directed by management.




 Qualifications

 EDUCATION & EXPERIENCE

Four years of full-time experience in data analysis, data research, data compilation; and/or reporting work.

OR 

A bachelor's degree from an accredited college or university with a major in engineering, basic science, computer science, environmental studies, mathematics, statistics or a related field; plus two years of the required experience.

OR 

A bachelor’s degree from an accredited college or university; plus three years of the required experience.

 About the Role
We are seeking a highly skilled and motivated Business Analyst to join our dynamic Customer Experience team. The ideal candidate will possess a keen analytical mind, a deep understanding of customer behavior, and the ability to translate complex data into actionable insights. As a Business Analyst, you will play a critical role in optimizing our customer experience strategy, driving data-driven decisions, and enhancing overall customer satisfaction.

 You Will

 About Us:
Community of Hope is a mission-driven, innovative, and rapidly growing nonprofit. For over 40 years, we have provided healthcare, housing, and supportive services for under-resourced, underserved and people experiencing homelessness in Washington, DC. As a Federally Qualified Health Center, we provide medical, dental, emotional wellness, and care coordination services for the whole family at three locations in DC. Community of Hope also strongly emphasizes maternal and child health, with midwifery practice and the only free-standing birth center in DC. In 2020, Community of Hope provided about 28,400 medical visits, 7,000 dental visits, and 10,000 behavioral health visits for about 11,000 patients. Community of Hope provides community walk-in COVID testing and COVID vaccines. Community of Hope is also one of the largest providers in DC of housing and support services for families and individuals experiencing homelessness. Through providing these programs, we live out our mission to improve health and end family and individual homelessness to make Washington, DC, more equitable.
We were selected as one of The Washington Post 150 Top Workplaces in 2024 and 6 other times since 2014 based on feedback from our staff.

Job Summary
 How to Apply
We ask that you include a cover letter for your application to be considered. Please attach it to the first page of your resume. The cover letter should address your specific interest in the position and outline experience that directly relates to it.
The target salary range for this position is $70,000-85,000.
 Who Are We?
The School of Dentistry (SoD) Dental Informatics IT department has an exciting opportunity for an INTERMEDIATE DATA ANALYST. You will be responsible for managing and creating Tableau dashboards, assisting in the development of data pipelines, and enhancing our analytics services.
Our organization supports faculty, staff, and students to further SoD's mission areas of teaching and learning, research, healthcare, and administration. We operate numerous health clinics, classrooms, research labs, conference rooms, and a museum, allowing us to support a diverse IT ecosystem. Dental Informatics prioritizes employee development through project opportunities, cross-unit collaboration, and the university's professional development catalog.
 What You'll Do as an Intermediate Data Analyst

You will consult with clinics, academic departments, and research areas to analyze requests and define business requirements.
You will have a hand in furthering data automation and developing analysis.
You will prepare various data products, visualizations, and reports for various customers, such as researchers, faculty leadership, clinical directors, and finance colleagues.
You will learn about Tableau, SQL, and Python
You will collaborate with other data analysts, developers, and the larger Dental Informatics team
You will work closely with other units on campus to leverage University-wide tools and services (e.g. Business Intelligence Community of Practice) as well as national networks (e.g. Healthcare Data and Analytics Association)
You will also leverage industry-leading practices to improve the functionality, reproducibility, and overall value of our data. Examples include machine learning and natural language processing.
You will have a combination of on-campus responsibilities and remote work opportunities.
You will report to the Assistant Director of Data Analytics and Development.

 Required Qualifications for Intermediate Data Analyst

BA or BS in quantitative field
3 to 5 years of experience
Familiarity with and experience building Tableau dashboards
Experience with creating charts, graphs, and reports and working with users to improve understanding
Experience with SQL
Experience with a variety of databases (Oracle, MySQL, PostGreSQL)
Demonstrated ability to apply new or different ways of thinking to creatively solve problems

 Work at SoD?
The School of Dentistry is consistently ranked as the #1 dental school in the United States and the world. We embrace diversity in many forms and champion diversity of thought and culture. Our Mission, core values, and additional information about our College can be found on our college website. Life insurance

Work-Life Programs to strengthen a workplace culture that supports personal and family life, including child care, elder care, lactation resources, and mental and emotional health services
